The pragmatic public transport (MHD) will introduce the chip into their ticketing system on Wednesday
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of the Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragosa Agency for Transport) as the date on which the first passengers, trams and buses, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, it is accessible to approximately 100,000 people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and both have it registered on their smartcard at the information points and offices of Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located at the Muzeum metro stations, Mëstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajskázahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility of buying coupons over the Internet on the Dopravní pondnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people took advantage of the service in the morning.
Those who will start using the online store may permanently forget the windows in the metro stations, where they have to walk impatience in long queues so far in order to obtain paper tickets.
Indeed, they will buy their coupons over the Internet and they will be registered on their Opencard card in one of the 13 Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these contact points, there is at the disposal of passengers a window with trained staff, which will help interested people with internet purchase and, in addition, will record the coupon they bought on their map," says the spokesperson for the Martin Opatrný project.
In addition to the libraries, it will also be possible to record the electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the stations of metro Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," said Opatrný.
An automatic will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just insert the Opencard chip card and the previously purchased coupon will register itself on the card.
