Talk in sleep
Some kids talk at night.
I do not refer to those who wake up very awake by telling us something that happened the day before, but to the children who speak during their sleep.
The first time this happens you may be surprised, but it really doesn't matter.
It's a benign sleep disturbance called sleepiness.
This is quite common, especially in children and adolescents.
I'm sure there's more than one talking during the night.
This phenomenon may appear very sporadic (once in life, for example associated with an episode of severe fever), or more periodically (every day, once a week, once a month ...), the day after the child no longer remembers anything.
There is no single cause that determines its appearance
They are often related to other sleep disturbances such as nightmares, night terrors, night sickness (beeping in bed) or sleepwalking, but this is not always the case.
As we have said before, they can also be associated with very strong fevers, stress or overexcitement situations.
Anyway, it's a little studied phenomenon.
The intensity with which it occurs is also very variable.
He may speak with a quiet little voice, with isolated words, murmurs or instead with screams, cries, long speeches ...
In the event that sleepiness becomes very frequent, it would be wise to observe the child and consult a specialist, to check if there is a problem that causes much anxiety and to get an explanation for this problem.
