The intervention of the governments of Belgium, the Netherlands and Luxembourg had been made necessary after the French bank BNP Paribas reported that it had refused to acquire its competitor in full shipwreck since it lost EUR 2 billion (US 2.9 billion) in the crisis of risky real estate loans in the United States.
Fortis employs 85,000 people and is one of the twenty largest European banks and ten largest insurers.
"This is not lost money," said Dutch Finance Minister Wouter Bos yesterday.
In return, a right to vote in the bank and influence is regained.
It is just something that savers and households now appreciate that the times are making an announcement of uncertainty."
